<db:section xml:id="QRhiViewport">
<db:title>QRhiViewport::QRhiViewport(float <db:emphasis>x</db:emphasis>, float <db:emphasis>y</db:emphasis>, float <db:emphasis>w</db:emphasis>, float <db:emphasis>h</db:emphasis>, float <db:emphasis>minDepth</db:emphasis> = 0.0f, float <db:emphasis>maxDepth</db:emphasis> = 1.0f)</db:title>
<db:para>Constructs a viewport description with the rectangle specified by <db:code role="parameter">x</db:code>, <db:code role="parameter">y</db:code>, <db:code role="parameter">w</db:code>, <db:code role="parameter">h</db:code> and the depth range <db:code role="parameter">minDepth</db:code> and <db:code role="parameter">maxDepth</db:code>.</db:para>
<db:note>
<db:para><db:code role="parameter">x</db:code> and <db:code role="parameter">y</db:code> are assumed to be the bottom-left position. <db:code role="parameter">w</db:code> and <db:code role="parameter">h</db:code> should not be negative, the viewport will be ignored by <db:link xlink:href="qrhicommandbuffer.xml#setViewport">QRhiCommandBuffer::setViewport</db:link>() otherwise.</db:para>
</db:note>
